<br>
I used fire pet it only makes sense, the damage sheild hits for so mo much more than your ds) I then started around the room from the left side.  you should have no problem doing this you will get all single pulls and one double pull.  I have found that you and your pet combined need to outdamage your pets damage sheild for maximum experience as soon as your able to do this mana efficiently I would will pay off big time in the area of exp. <br>
<br>
 When you reach lvl 29 you will easily be able to take the needs and the boglings in the near by room if you wish (around lvl 26-29 I started to take 2 boglings you pass on the way to the needelites because I could single pull them. I would often have lots of time until the next time so I would use this time to practice my off magic classes (ie. divination, alteration, abjuration)  I would suggest using the lowest lvl spells you have in that type.  For example I used sense heading and raised my divination to max in just one night fighting the needelites.  You can make hotkeys and macros that cut back on the mindless clicking of raising magic skill levels.  <br>
<br>
This is also a good place to raise your dodge skill I did.  Just make sure you have on your phantom armor for the regain.  Around lvl 30 the boglings go lt blue and are no longer worth it and the needelites xp starts to slow down.  Taking 5 and 6 hours for a lvl I decided to move on at lvl 32 I ventured to DSP for information on the zelniaks and mushrooms check out the 29-34 where to hunt section.   <p><a href=mailto:RavianVarior@hotmail.com><b>Ravian Varior</b></a> <a href=http://www.legionoffyre.net><b>{Legion of Fyre}</b></a><br><b>LVL 33 Erudite Mage</b><br><a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/bxegony >Xegony</a>
